# ============================================================
# ORGANIZATION CORE ARCHITECTURE
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: architecture
domain: organization
scope: organization.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines the canonical architectural role of organization in CivilizationOS.

## design_intent
Organization is the bounded structure that arranges
collective roles,
shared authority,
membership,
execution topology,
and internal coordination.

Organization is broader than company.
A company may be one form of organization,
but organization also covers non-company collective structures
that still require bounded roles and reviewable authority.

## architectural_position
Organization connects:
- collective identity
- membership structure
- role topology
- company-linked and non-company execution
- policy/governance boundary
- communication and coordination

## required_behavior
- organization identity must remain explicit
- membership scope must remain explicit
- role topology must remain explicit
- authority boundary must remain explicit
- current and historical organization states must remain distinguishable

## state_model
The organization domain distinguishes:
- proposed organization
- active organization
- restricted organization
- suspended organization
- historical organization
- dissolved organization

## canonical_rules
- membership does not imply unlimited authority
- organization truth must not be replaced by projection
- company-linked organization and generic organization must remain distinguishable
- historical trace must remain preserved
- ambiguous organization authority fails closed

## actor_boundary
- organization owner/founder
- operator
- member
- reviewer
- regulator
- adapter

## review_checklist
- identity is explicit
- membership model is explicit
- role topology is explicit
- state model is explicit
